                            <comment id="13102176" author="brandon.williams" created="Sat, 10 Sep 2011 23:28:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Disabling HH means hints won&apos;t be written, not that existing hints won&apos;t be delivered.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13102182" author="jeromatron" created="Sat, 10 Sep 2011 23:53:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sounds like&lt;br/&gt;
1) the logging happens even when it&apos;s disabled.&lt;br/&gt;
2) I double checked in the StorageProxy.HintedHandoffEnabled and it is set to false&lt;br/&gt;
3) there were probably some residual hints that were never delivered before disabling HH.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13118687" author="jbellis" created="Sat, 1 Oct 2011 05:55:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This isn&apos;t the first time the continued handoff messages post-disable have confused someone.  Patch to avoid these is attached.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13118832" author="slebresne" created="Sat, 1 Oct 2011 15:17:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1, committed&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
